article.description: Anton Wilson pumped in five 3-pointers and scored 18 points to lead Detroit to a 75-68 comeback win over Wright State on Sunday.
article.headline: Detroit overtakes Wright State and hangs on for 75-68 win
article.linkText: Detroit overtakes Wright State and hangs on for 75-68 win
article.story: DETROIT -- Anton Wilson pumped in five 3-pointers and scored 18 points to lead Detroit to a 75-68 comeback win over Wright State on Sunday. Jaleel Hogan added 13 points for Detroit (10-11, 4-6 Horizon League), Josh McFolley had 12 and Jarod Williams 11. The Titans controlled the glass 31-21 and dominated at the free throw line, hitting 28 of 37 to Wright State's 7 of 10. Trailing by 10 late in the first half, Detroit took control with a 21-5 run stretching across both sides of the intermission to go ahead 46-40 with 12:51 left to play. Wilson had four of his 3-pointers during the stretch. Wright State (13-10, 7-3) stayed close, retaking the lead 64-63 on JT Yoho's 3-point play before two free throws from Hogan put Detroit on top for good with 2:24 left. Yoho led the Raiders with a career-high 31 points and Mark Alstork added 14.
